Doyin Okupe, the Director-General of Peter Obi Campaign Organization has said that the Presidential candidate of the Labour Party (LP) will announce his substantive Vice Presidential candidate between Wednesday, July 6 to Friday, July 8. Okupe who made this disclosure while featuring on Channels Television’s Politics Today on Tuesday said that Senator Datti Baba Ahmed and others are being considered for the position. Speaking on the programme, Okupe said Obi and the LP were looking out for a young vibrant politician from the north with a measure of intellect, sound background, pedigree and education. Okupe, who is currently Obi’s placeholder, said the former Governor of Anambra State will announce his running mate latest by Friday. He said, “Senator Datti is being considered. Others are being considered too. These things will be decided this week [it’s going to be an announcement from Peter Obi] very very likely. “I’m sure about Senator Darti being the running mate but I know that this matter will be concluded before Friday. “Senator Datti is being considered along with other people whom we’ve engaged and talked with. “The emphasis is this, we’re looking for a young vibrant politician of northern extraction with a measure of intellect, sound background, pedigree and education. That is what we’re looking at,” he said. -Advertisement- POLL In order to beat the deadline set by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), the Labour Party and Peter Obi had picked Dr Doyin Okupe to temporarily hold the running mate position until a substantive vice presidential candidate is announced.